<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80b5ec03-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s3146"><num value="3146">§ 3146.</num><heading> Effect on other federal laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">This subchapter does not supersede or impair any authority otherwise granted by federal law to provide for the establishment of specific wage rates.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id80b5ec04-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1152">116 Stat. 1152</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
